This markup blog website is built using the Node.js runtime, powered by the Express framework, and utilizes MongoDB as its database. The website enables users to Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) blog posts effortlessly. Through a user-friendly interface, writers can compose and publish articles, which are then stored in the MongoDB database. The Express framework handles routing, allowing for smooth navigation and interaction. This website harmoniously merges the power of Node.js, the convenience of Express, and the flexibility of MongoDB to provide an efficient platform for managing and sharing blog content
